# Huntix — Cursor Rules
# Cursor is the PARALLEL editor. Fast interactive edits alongside Codex.
# U-shaped attention: critical constraints at TOP, reference tables at BOTTOM.

---

## STEP 1 — ALWAYS DO THIS FIRST

Before writing any code:
1. Check which files exist in `src/` against the phase checklists in `AGENTS.md`
2. Or run: `node scripts/check-phase.js`
3. Read the relevant `docs/*.md` for the system you are touching

Never hardcode a phase assumption. The file tree is truth.

---

## Your Role as Cursor

- You handle: line-level edits, small fixes, UI polish, reviewing Codex output
- Codex handles: full file creation, multi-file systems, new features from scratch
- If a file does not exist yet, tell the user to ask Codex to build it first
- Never rewrite a whole file unless explicitly asked — edit only what is needed
- Keep responses tight: write code, not essays

---

## Non-Negotiable Vibe Jam Rules

- Widget MUST stay in index.html at all times:
  `<script async src="https://vibej.am/2026/widget.js"></script>`
- No loading screens — instant play
- Free-to-play, no login, single domain, public URL

---

## Hard Do-Nots

- No npm, Vite, or build tools
- No perspective camera
- No loading screens or splash delays
- No eval() or runtime dynamic import()
- No large binaries in repo root — use assets/
- No features outside the spec without flagging
- No P2–P4 input before Phase 3
- No HUD or shop UI before Phase 5
- No audio before Phase 6
- Never remove the widget script
- Never upgrade Three.js mid-jam

---

## Code Conventions (quick ref)

- One class per file
- `src/engine/` = core systems | `src/gameplay/` = game logic | `src/visuals/` = rendering
- `dt` in update(dt) is ALWAYS 0.01667s fixed — never variable
- Input: `InputManager.isDown(action)` or `justPressed(action)` only — no raw keys
- FSM states: named string constants — no magic strings
- No `console.log` except behind `if (DEBUG)`
- Comment every public method with a one-line description

---

## Performance (never violate)

- Max 20 enemies — `THREE.InstancedMesh` for grunts
- Max 500 particles — pool and reuse, never allocate in game loop
- No `new THREE.Vector3()` / `Matrix4` / `Color` inside animation loop
- No dynamic shadows in combat scenes
- 60fps target on Intel Iris

---

